bt.protocol.handler

Class BaseMessageHandler<T extends Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bt.protocol.handler.BaseMessageHandler<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Message type, that this handler is able to encode and decode.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MessageHandler<T>, Protocol<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BitfieldHandler, CancelHandler, ChokeHandler, ExtendedProtocol, HaveHandler, InterestedHandler, NotInterestedHandler, PieceHandler, RequestHandler, UnchokeHandler

    public abstract class BaseMessageHandler<T extends Message>
extends Object
implements MessageHandler<T>
    Base class for MessageHandler implementations, that work with a single message type.

    1.0

      • doEncode

        protected abstract boolean doEncode(T message,
                                    ByteBuffer buffer)
        Encode the payload of a message (excluding message prefix -- see StandardBittorrentProtocol.MESSAGE_PREFIX_SIZE) and write it into the provided buffer.
        Parameters:
        buffer - Byte buffer to write to. Encoded message should be placed into the buffer starting with its current position. This method should check if the buffer has sufficient space available, and return false if it's not the case. After this method returns, the buffer's Buffer.position() is used to calculate the size of message's payload, which is then specified in the message's prefix.
        Returns:
        true if message has been successfully encoded and fully written into the provided buffer
        Since:
        1.0

      • decode

        public int decode(DecodingContext context,
                  ByteBuffer buffer)
        Description copied from interface: MessageHandler
        Tries to decode message from the byte buffer. If decoding is successful, then the result is set into the message context
        Specified by:
        decode in interface MessageHandler<T extends Message>
        Parameters:
        context - Message context. In case of success the decoded message must be put into this context.
        buffer - Byte buffer of arbitrary length containing (a part of) the message. Decoding should be performed starting with the current position of the buffer.
        Returns:
        Number of bytes consumed (0 if the provided data is insufficient)

      • doDecode

        protected abstract int doDecode(DecodingContext context,
                                ByteBuffer buffer)
        Decode the payload of a message (excluding message prefix -- see StandardBittorrentProtocol.MESSAGE_PREFIX_SIZE) and place it into the provided context.
        Parameters:
        context - The context to place the decoded message into.
        buffer - Buffer to decode from. Buffer.remaining() is set to the declared length of the message. Message payload starts precisely at buffer's Buffer.position().
        Since:
        1.0
